<emphasis id="ED8A4AFE7936BA214BEB19D25B475E00" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">L. teresinarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="451F8B8B01A1FA827D05869E004D41FD" genus="L." lsidName="L. subterranea" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="subterranea">
<emphasis id="09925EF8455FD2630341D959BEBE5EB3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">L. subterranea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the relationships among the dorsal, anal and caudal fins (i.e., independent in the first vs. broadly joined in the second), as well as by the shape of the hood of the male copulatory organ (i.e., broad distal lateral ends in 
<taxonomicName id="BB2AF755F2DB5182790374B28105BC6B" genus="L." lsidName="L. teresinarum" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="teresinarum">
<emphasis id="AC1F05B8A8D6CB4CC401D0014C2D37A4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">L. teresinarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. conical in 
<taxonomicName id="E7081740D06B2F3E358C7B8B4E314D7F" genus="L." lsidName="L. subterranea" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="subterranea">
<emphasis id="E010C42190058B0CEA8B5880EEF18784" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">L. subterranea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and pointed out that 
<taxonomicName id="EF36910884D44F12A725DAF79BB155C1" genus="L." lsidName="L. teresinarum" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="teresinarum">
<emphasis id="9420010994A0A7DF2D7BDCB6707031FB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">L. teresinarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares both characters states with 
<taxonomicName id="F5B9621BF101D88236426516E9CFC67B" genus="L." lsidName="L. dentata" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="dentata">
<emphasis id="7C04394C554B77693664F8DD605FC32A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">L. dentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Evidence from molecular data (
<bibRefCitation id="8684A4DCEA45771F1F891FBBEA0CBC30" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2011.06.015" author="Garcia-Machado, E" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetic and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="470 - 483" refId="B12" refString="Garcia-Machado, E, Hernandez, D, Garcia-Debras, A, Chevalier-Monteagudo, P, Bernatchez, L, Casane, D, 2011. Molecular phylogeny and phylogeography of the Cuban cave-fishes of the genus Lucifuga: Evidence for cryptic allopatric diversity. Molecular Phylogenetic and Evolution 61: 470 - 483, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2011.06.015" title="Molecular phylogeny and phylogeography of the Cuban cave-fishes of the genus Lucifuga: Evidence for cryptic allopatric diversity." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2011.06.015" volume="61" year="2011">
<normalizedToken id="079BEA3D8C81B29FFDC097D3ABEF641D" originalValue="García-Machado">Garcia-Machado</normalizedToken>
et al. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
) and morphological considerations indicate that this species is invalid and will be regarded as a synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="9642F133044551F348E0AB47DE63546C" genus="L." lsidName="L. subterranea" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="subterranea">
<emphasis id="777854EB8C29B1E37A3CB6C379CCBC7D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">L. subterranea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. All measures from the four specimens examined were included within 
<taxonomicName id="F77A116374AC865F0B4F1961B89A2293" genus="L." lsidName="L. subterranea" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="subterranea">
<emphasis id="6096874040B8CBF7F9509110CF66A3D9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">L. subterranea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Previous descriptions have indicated that 
<taxonomicName id="C1BFE9B3AAD1CE4E8F9828CFA15EB32F" genus="L." lsidName="L. subterranea" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="subterranea">
<emphasis id="55CA81890641E6936D92D3B1BF6564AC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">L. subterranea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a caudal fin broadly joined to dorsal and anal fins (
<bibRefCitation id="B2BD5F30B85E4E3F0EEE98708B2218DD" author="Poey, F" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B24" refString="Poey, F, 1858. Memorias Sobre la Historia Natural de la Isla de Cuba, Acompanadas de Sumarios Latinos y Frases en Frances, Imprenta de Barcina, Habana, 442 pp." title="Memorias Sobre la Historia Natural de la Isla de Cuba, Acompanadas de Sumarios Latinos y Frases en Frances, Imprenta de Barcina, Habana, 442 pp." year="1858">Poey 1858</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="4AD8A74838FD5877A1AFD1BAD8F15A3E" author="Cohen, DM" journalOrPublisher="Proceeding of the Biological Society of Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="133 - 144" refId="B1" refString="Cohen, DM, Robins, CR, 1970. A New Ophidioid Fish (genus Lucifuga) from a Limestone sink, New Providence Island, Bahamas. Proceeding of the Biological Society of Washington 83: 133 - 144" title="A New Ophidioid Fish (genus Lucifuga) from a Limestone sink, New Providence Island, Bahamas." volume="83" year="1970">Cohen and Robins 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="7A05A19BCC16B3869CCC3F8FE9CA411F" author="Nalbant, TT" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B22" refString="Nalbant, TT, 1981. A Study of the Subterranean Species of Lucifuga from Cuba, with the Description of Lucifugasimile sp. n. (Pices, Ophidiiformes, Bythitidae). Resultats des expeditions bio-speologiques cubano-roumanianes a Cuba, Bucarest, Romania, 185-190." title="A Study of the Subterranean Species of Lucifuga from Cuba, with the Description of Lucifugasimile sp. n. (Pices, Ophidiiformes, Bythitidae). Resultats des expeditions bio-speologiques cubano-roumanianes a Cuba, Bucarest, Romania, 185 - 190." year="1981">Nalbant 1981</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="7F8D774E17A29F12A07CB1BE26B673B1" author="Nielsen, JG" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B23" refString="Nielsen, JG, Cohen, DM, Markle, DF, Robins, CR, 1999. Ophidiiform Fishes of the World (Order Ophidiiformes). FAO Species Catalogue 18: I-XI + 1-178." title="Ophidiiform Fishes of the World (Order Ophidiiformes). FAO Species Catalogue 18: I-XI + 1 - 178." year="1999">Nielsen et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="BD6087ECAAA012D9621DEFA18915CADC" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1223.1.3" author="Moller, PR" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="23 - 46" refId="B20" refString="Moller, PR, Schwarzhans, W, Iliffe, TM, Nielsen, JG, 2006. Revision of the Bahamian cave-fishes of the genus Lucifuga (Ophidiiformes, Bythitidae), with description of a new species from islands on the Little Bahama Bank. Zootaxa 1223: 23 - 46, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1223.1.3" title="Revision of the Bahamian cave-fishes of the genus Lucifuga (Ophidiiformes, Bythitidae), with description of a new species from islands on the Little Bahama Bank." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1223.1.3" volume="1223" year="2006">
<normalizedToken id="0565920264EA2A71F9C77C1E574B79C9" originalValue="Møller">Moller</normalizedToken>
et al. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
). However, as noticed previously by 
<bibRefCitation id="32F5178CC6F366720DDF4A1597DE445F" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2011.06.015" author="Garcia-Machado, E" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetic and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="470 - 483" refId="B12" refString="Garcia-Machado, E, Hernandez, D, Garcia-Debras, A, Chevalier-Monteagudo, P, Bernatchez, L, Casane, D, 2011. Molecular phylogeny and phylogeography of the Cuban cave-fishes of the genus Lucifuga: Evidence for cryptic allopatric diversity. Molecular Phylogenetic and Evolution 61: 470 - 483, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2011.06.015" title="Molecular phylogeny and phylogeography of the Cuban cave-fishes of the genus Lucifuga: Evidence for cryptic allopatric diversity." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2011.06.015" volume="61" year="2011">
<normalizedToken id="EF664E0115A19706CBB885A15E65DD10" originalValue="García-Machado">Garcia-Machado</normalizedToken>
et al. (2011)
</bibRefCitation>
four individuals collected at 
<normalizedToken id="07A2FC9EF33FD2924B84926689962249" originalValue="Baño">Bano</normalizedToken>
II cave have the caudal fin joined to the anal but free from the dorsal, a variant previously observed in 
<taxonomicName id="E98C7FC60A92B32EF3B2807E791F1C81" genus="L." lsidName="L. simile" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="simile">
<emphasis id="D76612D8A394A82C875F282977074E5C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">L. simile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="95EE02835CAD7197536FC8DF7BF0F606" author="Diaz-Perez, PA" journalOrPublisher="Revista Biologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="77 - 84" refId="B5" refString="Diaz-Perez, PA, Lima, AM, Garcia, E, 1987a. Morfologia Externa de Ejemplares Machos de Lucifuga simile Nalbant, 1981 (Ophidiiformes, Bythitidae). Revista Biologia 1: 77 - 84" title="Morfologia Externa de Ejemplares Machos de Lucifuga simile Nalbant, 1981 (Ophidiiformes, Bythitidae)." volume="1" year="1987 a">
<normalizedToken id="8C9E667683A199D169BDDDB3A513714A" originalValue="Díaz-Pérez">Diaz-Perez</normalizedToken>
et al. 1987a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="13181E1D283ACF6939DD0CF97AFEB6E5" author="Diaz-Perez, PA" journalOrPublisher="Revista Biologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="37 - 43" refId="B4" refString="Diaz-Perez, PA, 1988. Lucifuga teresinarum sp. n., Nueva Especie Cubana de Peces Troglobios. (Ophidiiformes, Bythitidae). Revista Biologia 2: 37 - 43" title="Lucifuga teresinarum sp. n., Nueva Especie Cubana de Peces Troglobios. (Ophidiiformes, Bythitidae)." volume="2" year="1988">
<normalizedToken id="BA082A97CC852B126951D5A5DB501CA7" originalValue="Díaz-Pérez">Diaz-Perez</normalizedToken>
1988
</bibRefCitation>
). The redefinition of 
<taxonomicName id="039F27A9E2949719E3BA912041106CA1" genus="L." lsidName="L. teresinarum" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="teresinarum">
<emphasis id="2E0525E1982659C82DC138F8AD4ABC54" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">L. teresinarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="EFFD8FE6E195E96A83AE6CFAD9E83A4C" genus="L." lsidName="L. subterranea" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="subterranea">
<emphasis id="678459E41B935637BC7D8A708CE4F63E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">L. subterranea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
increase the morphological variation in this species, only paralleled by 
<taxonomicName id="1F37B5BF1C609F9FD5C2AB0071D5B322" genus="L." lsidName="L. simile" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="simile">
<emphasis id="CF60C033424C600C6A8E0CDF3D7CDF5D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">L. simile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8040ECCE3967164F8C5EAEF1A6309D3C" author="Diaz-Perez, PA" journalOrPublisher="Revista Biologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="77 - 84" refId="B5" refString="Diaz-Perez, PA, Lima, AM, Garcia, E, 1987a. Morfologia Externa de Ejemplares Machos de Lucifuga simile Nalbant, 1981 (Ophidiiformes, Bythitidae). Revista Biologia 1: 77 - 84" title="Morfologia Externa de Ejemplares Machos de Lucifuga simile Nalbant, 1981 (Ophidiiformes, Bythitidae)." volume="1" year="1987 a">
<normalizedToken id="C320A3098ABF12C46DA7BF6F97AED127" originalValue="Díaz-Pérez">Diaz-Perez</normalizedToken>
et al. 1987a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
